"This setting determines the maximum size of the :term:`reference display "
"copy` derivative created from a :term:`master digital object` during digital"
" object upload. It is measured in pixels, and will be applied either to "
"height or width - whichever side reaches the pixel limit first."
msgstr ""
"この設定は、デジタルオブジェクトのアップロード中に:term:`master digital "
"object`から作成される:term:`reference display "
"copy`の派生物の最大サイズを決定します。サイズはピクセルで測定され、高さと幅のうち先にピクセル制限に達する側に適用されます。"

#: ../../user-manual/administer/settings.rst:1541
msgid ""
"One of AtoM's design assumptions is that the display dimensions of files "
"users upload typically will be too large to fit into the :term:`view page` "
"for an :term:`archival description`. Therefore, when you upload a file, AtoM"
" creates a :term:`reference display copy` for displaying in the view page."
